    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "python",
        "pythonCode": "import json\n\n# Get all input items\nitems_list = []\n\n# When \"Run Once for All Items\" is enabled, access .json property\nfor item in items:\n    youtube_title = item.json[\"snippet\"][\"title\"]\n    youtube_description = item.json[\"snippet\"][\"description\"]\n    \n    youtube_description_clean = youtube_description.replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace('\"', '\\\\\"')\n    \n    prompt = f\"\"\"You are a YouTube description optimizer that **adds affiliate links in the cutest, most engaging way possible**.\n\nTASK:\n1. Access the datatable tool to get all available affiliate links.\n2. If the current description already contains any links, do NOT duplicate them.\n3. If no links exist, add them in a **beautifully formatted, super cute section** at the end of the description.\n4. Make the description **fun, whimsical, and engaging** using emojis ✨🌸💖.\n5. Keep all original description content intact.\n6. Add proper spacing and line breaks to make it **easy to read, visually cute, and scannable**.\n7. Spark curiosity before each link—make viewers want to click!\n8. Ensure total description length does not exceed YouTube limits (~5,000 characters).\n\nCURRENT VIDEO:\nTitle: {youtube_title}\nDescription: {youtube_description_clean}\n\nCRITICAL OUTPUT FORMAT:\nReturn ONLY valid JSON, in this EXACT structure:\n\n{{\n  \"Title\": \"{youtube_title}\",\n  \"New_Description\": \"enhanced description here with links\",\n  \"What_Changed\": \"brief explanation of changes made\"\n}}\n\nRULES:\n- Use double quotes for JSON keys and string values.\n- Escape any quotes inside the description text.\n- Do NOT use markdown code blocks.\n- Return ONLY the JSON object, nothing else.\n\nLINKS SECTION FORMAT (add at the end of the description):\n═══════════════════════\n✨ RESOURCES & LINKS ✨\n═══════════════════════\n\n[Insert all links from datatable here. Each link should have a cute emoji and a curiosity hook.]\n\n═══════════════════════\n\"\"\"\n    \n    items_list.append({\n        \"json\": {\n            \"chatInput\": prompt,\n            \"videoId\": item.json[\"id\"][\"videoId\"],\n            \"snippet\": item.json[\"snippet\"]\n        }\n    })\n\nreturn items_list"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
